1
00:00:34,990 --> 00:00:37,180
This is Berk.

2
00:00:37,210 --> 00:00:41,510
It's 12 days North of hopeless and a few degrees South of freezing to death.

3
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:45,740
It's located solidly on the Meridian of Misery.

4
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:49,920
My village. In a word: sturdy.

5
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:54,880
It's been here for seven generations but every single building is new.

6
00:00:55,490 --> 00:00:59,740
We have fishing, hunting, and a charming view of the sunsets.

7
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:02,100
The only problems are the pests.

8
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:06,210
You see, most places have mice or mosquitoes.

9
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,270
We have...

10
00:01:12,340 --> 00:01:13,640
Dragons.

11
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:17,300
Most people would leave, but not us.

12
00:01:17,510 --> 00:01:18,520
We're Vikings.

13
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,950
We stubbornness issues.

14
00:01:23,180 --> 00:01:24,410
My name is Hiccup.

15
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:28,020
Great name, I know. But it's not the worst.

16
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:31,240
Parents believe a hideous name will frighten off Gnomes and Trolls.

17
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:34,170
Like our charming Viking demeanor wouldn't do that.

18
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:36,320
'Morning.

19
00:01:38,620 --> 00:01:40,320
What are you doing here? Get inside!

20
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:43,160
Get back inside!

21
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:50,610
Hiccup! What is he doing out again... What are you doing out? Get inside!

22
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:54,320
That's Stoick the Vast, Chief of the tribe.

23
00:01:54,570 --> 00:01:58,910
They say that when he was a baby he popped a Dragon's head clean off its shoulders.

24
00:01:59,470 --> 00:02:00,900
Do I believe it? Yes, I do.

25
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,840
What have we got?

26
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:06,090
Gronckles, Nadders, Zipplebacks... Oh, and hordes of Monstruous Nightmares.

27
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,480
Any Night Furys?

28
00:02:08,640 --> 00:02:11,000
- None so far.  - Good.

29
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,830
Light the torches!

30
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:22,010
Oh, nice of you to join the party. I thought you'd been carried off.

31
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:27,000
Who? Me? Nah, come on... I'm way too muscular for their taste.

32
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:29,830
They wouldn't know what to do with all... this.

33
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:32,600
Well, they need toothpicks, don't they?

34
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:36,770
The meathead with the attitude and interchangeable hands, is Gobber.

35
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:39,230
I have been his apprentice ever since I was little.

36
00:02:39,490 --> 00:02:41,320
Well, littler

37
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:45,860
We move to the moor defenses. We'll counterattack with the catapults.

38
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,710
See? Old village. Lots and lots of new houses.

39
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,720
Fire!

40
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:56,150
Oh, and that's Fishlegs

41
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,060
Snotlout

42
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,930
The twins, Ruffnut and Tuffnut...

43
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:00,280
And...

44
00:03:02,610 --> 00:03:03,900
Astrid.

45
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:16,400
Aww, their job is so much cooler.

46
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:20,970
Oh, come on. Let me out, please. I need to make my mark!

47
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:23,940
Oh, you have made plenty of marks. All in the wrong places.

48
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:28,170
Please, 2 minutes. I'll kill a dragon. My life will get infinitely better.

49
00:03:28,530 --> 00:03:29,750
I might even get a date.

50
00:03:29,930 --> 00:03:32,370
You can't lift a hammer. You can't swing an axe.

51
00:03:32,370 --> 00:03:34,030
You can't even throw one of these.

52
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:39,310
Okay, fine, but this will throw it for me.

53
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:43,580
See, now this right here is what I'm talking about.

54
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:46,020
But it... it's a mild calibration issue.

55
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:49,250
Hiccup, if you ever want to get out there to fight dragons

56
00:03:49,350 --> 00:03:50,750
you need to stop all....

57
00:03:51,420 --> 00:03:52,220
this.

58
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:54,140
But you just pointed to all of me.

59
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:55,960
Yes, that's it.

60
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,240
Stop being all of you.

61
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,970
- Oh...  - Oh, yes.

62
00:04:00,170 --> 00:04:03,150
You sir, are playing a dangerous game...

63
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:07,380
keeping this much raw Vikingness contained.

64
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:10,120
- There will be consequences!  - I take my chances.

65
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,380
Sword, sharpened, now!

66
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:15,670
One day I'll get out there.

67
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:20,370
Because killing a dragon is everything around here.

68
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:25,110
A Nadderhead is sure to get me at least noticed.

69
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:26,400
Gronckles are tough.

70
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:29,730
Taking down one of those would definitely get me a girlfriend.

71
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:32,370
A Zippleback: ...

72
00:04:33,670 --> 00:04:36,180
exotic, two heads, twice the status.

73
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:37,640
They found the sheep!

74
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:39,880
Concentrate fire over the lower bank!

75
00:04:40,090 --> 00:04:40,610
Hurry up!

76
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:42,010
Fire!

77
00:04:42,690 --> 00:04:45,430
And then, there's the Monstruous Nightmare.

78
00:04:45,550 --> 00:04:48,470
Only the best Vikings go after those.

79
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:52,180
They have this nasty habit of setting themselves on fire.

80
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,100
Reload!

81
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:57,270
I'll take care of this.

82
00:04:58,130 --> 00:05:02,460
But the ultimate prize is the dragon no one's ever seen.

83
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,780
We call it the...

84
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:05,800
- Night Fury!  - Get down!

85
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:11,020
Jump!

86
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:15,640
This thing never steals food, never shows itself, and...

87
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,500
never misses.

88
00:05:18,510 --> 00:05:21,590
No one has ever killed a Night Fury.

89
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:23,570
That's why I'm going to be the first.

90
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:27,060
Mind the fort, Hiccup. They need me out there.

91
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,490
Stay! Put!

92
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:30,960
There.

93
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,190
You know what I mean.

94
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:37,000
- Hiccup, what are you doing?  - Come back here!

95
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:39,330
Yeah, I know, Be right back!

96
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,620
Mind yourself!

97
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:50,230
The devils still have some juice in them.

98
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:01,660
Come on.

99
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:04,310
Give me something to shoot at. Give me something to shoot at.

100
00:06:26,530 --> 00:06:29,160
Oh! I hit it? Yes, I hit it!

101
00:06:29,340 --> 00:06:31,300
Did anybody see that?

102
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,640
Except for you.

103
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:42,750
- Do not let them escape!  - Right!

104
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:03,160
You're all out.

105
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:12,330
Oh, and there's one more thing you need to know...

106
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:24,600
Sorry, Dad.

107
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,910
Okay, but I hit a Night Fury.

108
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:37,360
It's not like the last few times, Dad!

109
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,270
I mean, I really actually hit...

110
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,730
You guys were busy and I had a very clear shot.

111
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:45,440
It went down just off Raven Point. Let's get a search party out there before...

112
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,960
Stop!

113
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:49,260
Just, stop!

114
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,570
Every time you step outside disaster falls.

115
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:54,830
Can you not see that I have bigger problems?

116
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:58,450
Winter is almost here and I have an entire village to feed!

117
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:03,450
Between you and me, the village could do with a little less feeding, don't you think?

118
00:08:03,770 --> 00:08:05,780
This isn't a joke, Hiccup!

119
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:08,920
Why can't you follow the simplest orders?

120
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:12,860
I, I can't stop myself. I see a dragon and I have to just...

121
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:16,290
kill it. You know, it's who I am, Dad.

122
00:08:16,650 --> 00:08:21,810
Oh, you are many things, Hiccup, but a dragon killer is not one of them.

123
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:26,130
Get back to the house. Make sure he gets there.

124
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:28,640
I have his mess to clean up.

125
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:31,020
Quite the performance.

126
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:33,830
I've never seen any one mess up that badly. That helped!

127
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,810
Thank you. Thank you. I was trying.

128
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:42,760
- I really did hit one.  - Sure, Hiccup.

129
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:44,850
- He never listens.  - Well, it runs in the family.

130
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:47,790
And when he does, it's always with this disappointed scowl

131
00:08:47,830 --> 00:08:50,160
like someone skimped on the meat in his sandwich.

132
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:54,360
Excuse me, barmaid. I'm afraid you brought me the wrong offspring.

133
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:59,090
I ordered an extra large boy with beefy arms. Extra guts and glory on the side.

134
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,920
This here. This is a talking fish bone!

135
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:04,090
Now, you're thinking about this all wrong.

136
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:08,930
It's not so much what you look like. It's what's inside that he can't stand.

137
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:11,320
Thank you for summing that up.

138
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:15,440
Look, the point is, stop trying so hard to be something you're not.

139
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:18,310
I just want to be one of you guys.

140
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:31,270
Either we face them or they'll finish us.

141
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:34,050
It's the only way we'll be rid of them.

142
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:37,590
If we find the nest and destroy it, the dragons will leave.

143
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:39,390
They'll find another home.

144
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:42,270
One more search, before the ice sets in.

145
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,220
Those ships never come back.

146
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:47,200
We're Vikings. It's an occupational hazard.

147
00:09:47,510 --> 00:09:48,800
Now who's with me?

148
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:56,310
Alright... Those who stay will look after Hiccup.

149
00:09:58,130 --> 00:09:59,970
I'll pack my undies.

150
00:10:00,380 --> 00:10:02,900
No, I need you to stay, and train some new recruits.

151
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:09,610
Oh, perfect, yeah. And while I'm busy Hiccup can cover the store.

152
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:13,920
Molten steel, razor sharp blades, lots of time to himself...

153
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,660
What could possibly go wrong?

154
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,760
Oh, what am I going to do with him, Gobber?

155
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:19,350
Put him in training with the others.

156
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,490
- No, I'm serious.  - So am I.

157
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:24,750
He'd be killed before you let the first dragon out of its cage.

158
00:10:24,870 --> 00:10:26,610
- Oh, you don't know that.  - I do know that.

159
00:10:26,730 --> 00:10:28,380
- No£¬ you don't  - No, actually, I do.

160
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:31,360
- No, you don't.  - Listen, you know what he's like.

161
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:35,150
From the time he could crawl he's been... different.

162
00:10:36,350 --> 00:10:39,680
He doesn't listen. He has the attention span of a sparrow.

163
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:43,850
I take him fishing and he goes hunting for... for Trolls!

164
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:46,520
Trolls exist! They steal your socks.

165
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:49,350
But only the left ones. What's with that?

166
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:51,500
- When I was a boy...  - Oh, here we go.

167
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:54,510
My father told me to bang my head against a rock, and I did it.

168
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:57,210
I thought it was crazy, but I didn't question him.

169
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,220
And you know what happened?

170
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,400
- You got a headache.  - That rock split in two.

171
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:05,270
It taught me what a Viking could do, Gobber.

172
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:07,880
He could crush mountains, level forests,

173
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,340
tame seas!

174
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:14,030
Even as a boy I knew what I was, what I had to become...

175
00:11:14,970 --> 00:11:16,860
Hiccup is not that boy.

176
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:21,880
You can't stop him, Stoick. You can only prepare him.

177
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:26,610
I know it seems hopeless, but the truth is you won't always be around to protect him.

178
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:30,620
He's going to get out there again. He's probably out there now.

179
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,680
Oh, the Gods hate me.

180
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:53,620
Some people lose their knife or their mug.

181
00:11:53,690 --> 00:11:56,750
No, not me! I managed to lose an entire dragon.

182
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,220
Ow!

183
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:49,210
Oh, wow? I... I did it? Oh, I did it!

184
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:52,060
This fixes everything. Yes!

185
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,660
I have brought down this mighty beast!

186
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:25,030
I'm gonna kill you, dragon.

187
00:13:25,570 --> 00:13:29,080
I'm gonna... I'm gonna cut out your heart and take it to my father.

188
00:13:30,210 --> 00:13:31,110
I'm a Viking.

189
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,410
I'm a Viking!

190
00:14:08,210 --> 00:14:09,840
I did this.

191
00:15:24,510 --> 00:15:25,440
Hiccup.

192
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,420
Dad? Uh...

193
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:30,650
- I have to talk to you, Dad.  - I need to speak with you too, son.

194
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:34,660
- I think it's time you to learned to fight dragons.  - I don't want to fight dragons.

195
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,240
- What?  - What?

196
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:38,700
- Uh, you go first.  - No, no, you go first.

197
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:41,230
All right. You got your wish.

198
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:44,380
Dragon training. You start in the morning.

199
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:46,180
Oh man, I should have gone first.

200
00:15:46,350 --> 00:15:52,010
Uh, cause I was thinking. You know, we have a surplus of dragon fighting Vikings but...

201
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:56,670
do we have enough bread-making Vikings, or small home repair Vikings...

202
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,260
- You'll need this.  - I don't want to fight dragons.

203
00:16:00,420 --> 00:16:05,990
- Oh come on, yes you do.  - Rephrase. Dad, I can't kill dragons.

204
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,780
But you will kill dragons.

205
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:10,660
No, I'm really very extra sure that I won't.

206
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:13,050
- It's time, Hiccup.  - Can you not hear me?

207
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:15,660
This is serious, son.

208
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:20,610
When you carry this axe, you carry all of us with you.

209
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:26,600
Which means: You walk like us. You talk like us. You think like us.

210
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:31,160
- No more of... this.  - You just gestured to all of me.

211
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:34,930
- Deal?  - This conversation is feeling very one-sided.

212
00:16:34,980 --> 00:16:35,950
Deal?

213
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,390
Deal.

214
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:41,830
Good.

215
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,330
Train hard.

216
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:47,780
I'll be back. Probably.

217
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:51,700
And I'll be here, maybe.

218
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,610
Welcome to dragon training.

219
00:16:56,420 --> 00:16:57,940
No turning back.

220
00:17:15,820 --> 00:17:17,670
I hope I get some serious burns.

221
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:21,290
I'm hoping for some mauling, like on my shoulder or lower back.

222
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,810
Yeah, it's only fun if you get a scar out of it.

223
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:27,450
Yeah, no kidding, right? Pain, love it.

224
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,410
Oh, great, who let him in?

225
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:32,470
Lets get started. The recruit who does best,

226
00:17:32,470 --> 00:17:36,870
will win the honor of killing his first dragon in front of the entire village.

227
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:41,700
Hiccup already killed a Night Fury, so does that disqualify him or...?

228
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,990
Can I transfer to the class with the cool Vikings?

229
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:48,250
Don't worry. You're small and you're weak, That will make you a less of a target.

230
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:53,700
They'll see you as sick or insane and go after the more Viking-like teens instead.

231
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:56,450
Behind these doors are just a few of the

232
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:59,070
many species you will learn to fight.

233
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:01,310
- The Deadly Nadder.  - Speed: 8, Armor: 16.

234
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:04,550
- The Hideous Zippleback.  - 11 Stealth times two.

235
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:06,860
- The Monstrous Nightmare.  - Fire Power: 15.

236
00:18:07,330 --> 00:18:09,200
- The Terrible Terror.  - Attack: 8, Venom: 12.

237
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:10,900
Can you stop that!

238
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:15,430
- And the Gronckle.  - Jaw Strength: 8.

239
00:18:15,990 --> 00:18:17,890
Woah, woah, wait, aren't you going to teach us first?

240
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:21,020
I believe in learning on the job.

241
00:18:22,390 --> 00:18:26,960
Today is about survival. If you get blasted, you're dead.

242
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:29,780
Quick! What's the first thing you're going to need?

243
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:31,390
- A doctor?  - + 5 Speed?

244
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,350
- A shield?  - Shield. Go.

245
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:37,280
Your most important piece of equipment is your shield.

246
00:18:37,790 --> 00:18:40,370
If you must make a choice between a sword or a shield.

247
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,630
Take the shield.

248
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,810
- Get your hands off my shield.  - There's like a million shields.

249
00:18:44,020 --> 00:18:46,220
Take that one. It has a flower on it. Girls like flowers.

