00:49:27,660 --> 00:49:31,850
I'll see you back at the house. Great. Thanks for stopping by and...

503
00:49:31,890 --> 00:49:34,030
- the uh... breast hat.  - I hope you like the, umm... the hat.

504
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:38,220
Well, good night.

505
00:49:53,130 --> 00:49:55,500
Stay out of my way. I'm winning this thing!

506
00:49:55,580 --> 00:49:57,660
Good. Please. By all means.

507
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:13,010
This time! This time for sure!

508
00:50:21,370 --> 00:50:25,630
No! No, son-of-a half troll, rat-eating munch bucket...!

509
00:50:25,940 --> 00:50:26,960
Wait! Wait.

510
00:50:27,100 --> 00:50:28,130
So... later.

511
00:50:28,190 --> 00:50:30,670
- Oh, oh! Not so fast!  - I'm kinda late for...

512
00:50:30,960 --> 00:50:34,140
What! Late for what, exactly?

513
00:50:34,710 --> 00:50:37,490
Okay, quiet down. The Elder has decided.

514
00:50:49,190 --> 00:50:51,410
Boy, you've done it! You've done it, Hiccup!

515
00:50:51,630 --> 00:50:53,630
You get to kill the dragon!

516
00:50:56,440 --> 00:50:57,990
That's my boy!

517
00:50:58,130 --> 00:51:01,290
Yeah! Yes, I can't wait. I am so...

518
00:51:01,350 --> 00:51:03,500
leaving. We're Leaving.

519
00:51:03,540 --> 00:51:04,700
Let's pack up.

520
00:51:05,150 --> 00:51:07,730
Looks like you and me are taking a little vacation.

521
00:51:08,370 --> 00:51:09,410
Forever.

522
00:51:12,750 --> 00:51:14,120
Awww, man.

523
00:51:15,820 --> 00:51:19,420
What the...? Uh, w... what are you doing here?

524
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:21,590
I want to know what's going on.

525
00:51:22,190 --> 00:51:24,640
No one just get as good as you do.

526
00:51:25,200 --> 00:51:26,750
Especially... you.

527
00:51:26,940 --> 00:51:28,610
- Start talking.  - I... I...

528
00:51:28,700 --> 00:51:29,610
Are you training with someone?

529
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:30,830
Training? I didn't...

530
00:51:31,060 --> 00:51:32,740
It better not involve this.

531
00:51:32,820 --> 00:51:36,090
I know, this looks really bad but you see, this is...

532
00:51:38,980 --> 00:51:42,560
You're right. You're right. You're right. I... I'm through with the lies.

533
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:45,100
I've been making... outfits!

534
00:51:45,250 --> 00:51:48,050
So, you got me. It's time everyone knew.

535
00:51:48,160 --> 00:51:50,450
Drag me back. Go ahead. Here we go.

536
00:51:50,810 --> 00:51:52,690
Oww. Why would you do that?

537
00:51:52,910 --> 00:51:54,420
That's for the lies!

538
00:51:54,690 --> 00:51:57,760
And that's... for everything else!

539
00:51:57,890 --> 00:51:58,880
Oh man.

540
00:51:59,770 --> 00:52:01,040
Get down!

541
00:52:02,770 --> 00:52:04,250
Run! Run!

542
00:52:05,140 --> 00:52:10,370
No! No! It's okay. It's okay. She's a friend.

543
00:52:12,870 --> 00:52:13,800
You just scared him.

544
00:52:13,820 --> 00:52:15,190
I scared him?

545
00:52:16,980 --> 00:52:18,680
Who is him?

546
00:52:19,360 --> 00:52:23,210
Astrid, Toothless. Toothless, Astrid.

547
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:30,540
Dut, da da... We're dead.

548
00:52:32,060 --> 00:52:34,330
Woah, woah woah. Where do you think your going?

549
00:52:40,480 --> 00:52:43,110
Oh, great Odin! Don't. Oh, this is...

550
00:52:53,980 --> 00:52:56,600
Hiccup, get me down from here!

551
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:58,790
You have to give me a chance to explain.

552
00:52:58,830 --> 00:53:01,900
I am not listening to anything you have to say!

553
00:53:01,940 --> 00:53:04,870
Then I won't speak. Just let me show you.

554
00:53:06,560 --> 00:53:07,940
Please, Astrid.

555
00:53:23,950 --> 00:53:25,510
Now get me down!

556
00:53:25,680 --> 00:53:28,370
Toothless, down. Gently.

557
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:32,540
See, nothing to be afraid of.

558
00:53:36,060 --> 00:53:37,110
Toothless?

559
00:53:38,540 --> 00:53:41,130
What is wrong with you? Bad dragon!

560
00:53:42,160 --> 00:53:44,190
He's uh, he's not usually like this.

561
00:53:44,410 --> 00:53:45,360
Oh, no!

562
00:53:50,530 --> 00:53:52,920
Toothless, what are you doing? We need her to like us!

563
00:53:56,390 --> 00:53:58,510
And now he's spinning!

564
00:53:59,840 --> 00:54:02,090
Thank you for nothing you useless reptile!

565
00:54:03,600 --> 00:54:08,290
Okay, I am sorry, I'm sorry. Just get me off of this thing.

566
00:55:54,900 --> 00:55:57,860
Alright, I admit it. This is pretty cool.

567
00:55:59,130 --> 00:56:03,000
It's amazing. He's amazing.

568
00:56:05,930 --> 00:56:07,210
So what now?

569
00:56:08,540 --> 00:56:11,090
Hiccup, your final exam is tomorrow!

570
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:13,100
You know your gonna have to kill a...

571
00:56:14,210 --> 00:56:15,030
kill a dragon...

572
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:16,400
Don't remind me.

573
00:56:18,370 --> 00:56:19,670
Toothless, what happening?

574
00:56:21,790 --> 00:56:23,360
Whoa, what is it?

575
00:56:26,430 --> 00:56:27,570
Get down!

576
00:56:44,810 --> 00:56:46,780
- What's going on?  - I don't know.

577
00:56:46,870 --> 00:56:49,550
Toothless, you gotta get us out of here, bud.

578
00:56:52,330 --> 00:56:54,910
It looks like they're hauling in their kill.

579
00:56:55,820 --> 00:56:57,570
What does that make us?

580
00:57:40,930 --> 00:57:43,690
What my dad wouldn't give to find this.

581
00:57:59,800 --> 00:58:03,740
Oh, it's satisfying to know that all of our food has been dumped down a hole.

582
00:58:04,770 --> 00:58:06,630
They're not eating any of it.

583
00:58:21,710 --> 00:58:23,380
What... was that?

584
00:58:30,820 --> 00:58:33,470
Alright, bud, we gotta get out of here. Now!

585
00:58:43,120 --> 00:58:46,420
No, no, it totally makes sense. It's like a giant beehive.

586
00:58:46,770 --> 00:58:48,960
They're the workers, and that's their queen.

587
00:58:49,020 --> 00:58:51,920
It controls them. Let's find your dad.

588
00:58:51,960 --> 00:58:53,090
No, no.

589
00:58:53,890 --> 00:58:57,160
No. Not yet. They'll kill Toothless.

590
00:58:57,700 --> 00:58:59,720
Astrid, we have to think this through, carefully.

591
00:59:00,680 --> 00:59:03,760
Hiccup, we just discovered the dragon's nest.

592
00:59:03,840 --> 00:59:06,790
The thing we've been after since Vikings first sailed here.

593
00:59:06,980 --> 00:59:08,650
And you want to keep it secret?

594
00:59:08,970 --> 00:59:12,000
To protect your pet, dragon? Are you serious?

595
00:59:14,520 --> 00:59:15,650
Yes.

596
00:59:23,190 --> 00:59:25,220
Okay. Then what do we do?

597
00:59:25,680 --> 00:59:29,250
Just give me until tomorrow. I'll figure something out.

598
00:59:30,220 --> 00:59:31,280
Okay...

599
00:59:32,500 --> 00:59:34,000
That's for kidnapping me.

600
00:59:40,990 --> 00:59:43,660
That's for... everything else.

601
00:59:52,720 --> 00:59:54,450
What are you looking at?

602
00:59:59,300 --> 01:00:02,080
Well, I can show my face in public again.

603
01:00:04,970 --> 01:00:08,130
If someone had told me that in a few short weeks

604
01:00:08,520 --> 01:00:15,630
Hiccup will go from... well being... uh... Hiccup,

605
01:00:16,030 --> 01:00:18,990
to placing first in dragon training.

606
01:00:19,110 --> 01:00:23,570
Well, I would have tied him to a mast and shipped him off. For fear he'd gone mad.

607
01:00:24,750 --> 01:00:26,090
And you know it.

608
01:00:27,440 --> 01:00:29,420
But, here we are.

609
01:00:30,000 --> 01:00:35,020
And no ones more surprised or more proud than I am.

610
01:00:36,120 --> 01:00:39,170
Today my boy becomes a Viking!

611
01:00:40,080 --> 01:00:43,230
Today he becomes one of us!

612
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:49,010
Be careful with that dragon.

613
01:00:49,050 --> 01:00:50,840
It's not the dragon I'm worried about.

614
01:00:51,150 --> 01:00:52,450
What are you going to do?

615
01:00:52,600 --> 01:00:54,040
Put an end to this.

616
01:00:54,490 --> 01:00:55,740
I have to try.

617
01:00:56,310 --> 01:01:01,710
Astrid, if something goes wrong, just make sure they don't find Toothless.

618
01:01:02,290 --> 01:01:05,910
I will, just promise me it won't go wrong.

619
01:01:06,930 --> 01:01:08,130
It's time, Hiccup.

620
01:01:08,700 --> 01:01:10,140
Knock 'em dead.

621
01:01:33,700 --> 01:01:35,710
I'd have gone for the hammer.

622
01:01:39,590 --> 01:01:41,000
I'm ready.

623
01:02:05,520 --> 01:02:08,110
Go on Hiccup, give it to him!

624
01:02:11,900 --> 01:02:13,450
What is he doing?

625
01:02:16,330 --> 01:02:18,640
It's okay, it's okay.

626
01:02:26,700 --> 01:02:28,280
I'm not one of them.

627
01:02:32,860 --> 01:02:34,680
What's he thinking?

628
01:02:34,720 --> 01:02:35,870
Stop the fight!

629
01:02:36,170 --> 01:02:38,680
No! I need you all to see this.

630
01:02:40,140 --> 01:02:42,400
They're not what we think they are.

631
01:02:42,890 --> 01:02:44,510
We don't have to kill them.

632
01:02:46,080 --> 01:02:48,290
I said stop the fight!

633
01:02:56,200 --> 01:02:57,140
Out of my way!

634
01:02:57,180 --> 01:02:58,160
Hiccup!

635
01:03:19,380 --> 01:03:20,390
Hiccup!

636
01:03:26,810 --> 01:03:27,810
This way!

637
01:03:48,550 --> 01:03:49,940
Night Fury!

638
01:04:08,240 --> 01:04:10,200
Alright, Toothless. Go! Get out of here.

639
01:04:12,560 --> 01:04:13,960
Go, go!

640
01:04:14,320 --> 01:04:16,330
No, dad! Dad, he won't hurt you!

641
01:04:21,220 --> 01:04:22,560
Toothless, stop!

642
01:04:24,200 --> 01:04:26,180
No. No!

643
01:04:30,010 --> 01:04:31,490
Get him!

644
01:04:34,680 --> 01:04:36,390
No, no, please. Just don't hurt him

645
01:04:37,430 --> 01:04:38,730
Please. Don't hurt him

646
01:04:45,520 --> 01:04:47,360
Put it with the others.

647
01:04:49,810 --> 01:04:51,110
I should have known.

648
01:04:51,480 --> 01:04:52,890
I should have seen the signs.

649
01:04:52,970 --> 01:04:54,640
- Dad?  - We had a deal!

650
01:04:54,770 --> 01:04:58,710
I know! We did, but that was before I... Oh, it's all so messed up.

651
01:04:58,840 --> 01:05:02,170
So everything in that ring... A trick? A lie?

652
01:05:02,510 --> 01:05:05,110
I screwed up. I should have told you before now.

653
01:05:06,200 --> 01:05:10,510
Take this out on me, be mad at me, but please, just don't hurt Toothless.

654
01:05:10,890 --> 01:05:13,570
The dragon? That's what you're worried about?

655
01:05:14,030 --> 01:05:15,650
Not the people you almost killed?

656
01:05:15,690 --> 01:05:17,840
He was just protecting me! He's not dangerous.

657
01:05:18,230 --> 01:05:20,370
They've killed hundreds of us!

658
01:05:20,470 --> 01:05:24,740
And we've killed thousands of them. They defend themselves, that's all.

659
01:05:25,750 --> 01:05:27,670
They raid us because they have to.

660
01:05:28,130 --> 01:05:31,750
If they don't bring enough food back, they'll be eaten themselves.

661
01:05:32,090 --> 01:05:35,870
There's something else on their island, dad. It's a dragon-like...

662
01:05:36,240 --> 01:05:39,460
Their island? So, you've been to the nest?

663
01:05:39,610 --> 01:05:41,560
- Did I say nest?  - How did you find it?

664
01:05:41,600 --> 01:05:46,540
No, no, I didn't. Toothless did. Only a dragon can find the island.

665
01:05:48,230 --> 01:05:51,060
No, no, dad, no please. It's not what you think.

666
01:05:51,240 --> 01:05:54,360
You don't know what your up against. It's like nothing you've ever seen.

667
01:05:54,940 --> 01:05:57,890
Dad, please, I promise you. You can't win this one!

668
01:05:58,660 --> 01:06:00,070
Dad, no!

669
01:06:00,500 --> 01:06:03,500
For once in your life, would you please just listen to me!

670
01:06:07,260 --> 01:06:09,160
You've thrown your lot in with them.

671
01:06:09,860 --> 01:06:11,440
You're not a Viking.

672
01:06:13,210 --> 01:06:14,970
You're not my son!

673
01:06:18,680 --> 01:06:20,270
Ready the ships!

674
01:07:15,250 --> 01:07:16,550
Set sail!

675
01:07:16,670 --> 01:07:18,800
We head for Hell Hounds gate.

676
01:07:27,220 --> 01:07:29,710
Lead us home, devil.

677
01:07:50,680 --> 01:07:54,920
It's a mess. You must feel horrible.

678
01:07:55,510 --> 01:08:00,040
You've lost everything. Your father, your tribe, your best friend.

679
01:08:00,260 --> 01:08:02,160
Thank you for summing that up.

680
01:08:04,240 --> 01:08:07,050
Why couldn't I've killed that dragon, when I found him the woods?

681
01:08:07,930 --> 01:08:09,720
Would've been better for everyone.

682
01:08:09,870 --> 01:08:11,550
Yep, the rest of us would have done it.

683
01:08:12,990 --> 01:08:14,610
So, why didn't you?

684
01:08:17,510 --> 01:08:18,910
Why didn't you?

685
01:08:19,500 --> 01:08:21,970
I don't know. I couldn't.

686
01:08:22,140 --> 01:08:25,480
- That's not an answer.  - Why is this so important to you all of a sudden?

687
01:08:25,900 --> 01:08:29,220
Because I want to remember what you say, right now.

688
01:08:29,270 --> 01:08:32,650
Ah, for the love of... I was coward, I was weak.

689
01:08:33,040 --> 01:08:34,580
I wouldn't kill a dragon!

690
01:08:34,650 --> 01:08:35,900
You said wouldn't that time?

691
01:08:35,960 --> 01:08:37,930
Whatever, I wouldn't!

692
01:08:38,650 --> 01:08:42,130
300 years and I'm the first Viking who wouldn't kill a dragon.

693
01:08:46,240 --> 01:08:48,470
First to ride one though.

694
01:08:51,060 --> 01:08:52,010
So?

695
01:08:54,860 --> 01:08:58,090
I wouldn't kill him because he looked as frightened as I was.

696
01:08:59,160 --> 01:09:02,670
I looked at him and I saw myself.

697
01:09:04,820 --> 01:09:06,800
I bet he's really frightened now.

698
01:09:07,510 --> 01:09:09,140
What are you gonna do about it?

699
01:09:10,650 --> 01:09:13,370
Probably something stupid.

700
01:09:13,720 --> 01:09:15,640
Good, but you've already done that.

701
01:09:17,110 --> 01:09:18,860
Then something crazy!

702
01:09:20,150 --> 01:09:21,920
That's more like it.

703
01:09:30,680 --> 01:09:34,040
Sound your positions! Stay within earshot.

704
01:09:36,910 --> 01:09:41,390
Listen, Stoick, I was overhearing some of the men just now and well, you know...

705
01:09:41,420 --> 01:09:44,150
some of them are wondering what it is we're up to here?

706
01:09:44,260 --> 01:09:47,590
Not me of course. I know you are always the man with the plan.

707
01:09:47,720 --> 01:09:52,060
But some, not me, are wondering if there is in fact a plan at all...

708
01:09:52,430 --> 01:09:54,310
and what it might be?

709
01:09:54,420 --> 01:09:56,130
Find the nest and take it.

710
01:09:56,390 --> 01:10:00,780
Of course. Send them running. The old Viking fallback. Nice and simple.

711
01:10:09,330 --> 01:10:10,610
Step aside.

712
01:10:24,100 --> 01:10:25,790
Head to port.

713
01:10:30,420 --> 01:10:36,120
If you're planning on getting eaten, I'd definitely go with the Gronckle.

714
01:10:37,360 --> 01:10:41,400
You were wise to seek help from the world's most deadly weapon.

715
01:10:41,720 --> 01:10:42,360
It's me.

716
01:10:42,390 --> 01:10:44,760
- I love this plan!  - I didn't...

717
01:10:44,810 --> 01:10:47,630
You're crazy. I like that.

718
01:10:48,740 --> 01:10:51,100
So, what is the plan?

719
01:11:00,810 --> 01:11:03,020
That's not very encouraging.

720
01:11:03,330 --> 01:11:06,850
Oh, I was wondering where that went.

721
01:11:19,630 --> 01:11:22,140
Stay low, and ready your weapons.

722
01:11:38,670 --> 01:11:39,990
We're here.

723
01:12:12,430 --> 01:12:13,960
Wait, what are you... ?!

724
01:12:15,240 --> 01:12:17,670
It's okay... It's okay.

725
01:12:29,070 --> 01:12:30,180
Where are you going?

726
01:12:30,230 --> 01:12:33,060
You're gonna need something to help you hold on.

727
01:12:41,960 --> 01:12:46,330
When we crack this mountain open, all hell is gonna break loose.

728
01:12:46,340 --> 01:12:49,050
In my undies. Good thing I brought extras.

729
01:12:49,510 --> 01:12:52,590
No matter how this ends, it ends today.

730
01:13:48,270 --> 01:13:50,080
Is that it?

731
01:13:53,840 --> 01:13:56,370
We've done it!

732
01:14:04,200 --> 01:14:05,440
This isn't over!

733
01:14:05,670 --> 01:14:07,930
Form your ranks. Pull together!

734
01:14:21,620 --> 01:14:23,050
Get clear!

735
01:14:33,040 --> 01:14:35,700
Beards of Thor...! What is that?

736
01:14:39,940 --> 01:14:41,680
Odin, help us!

737
01:14:46,390 --> 01:14:48,570
- Catapults!  - Fire!

738
01:14:57,310 --> 01:14:59,610
- Get to the ships!  - No, nooo!

739
01:15:12,570 --> 01:15:14,560
- Not that one...  - I was a fool.

740
01:15:14,650 --> 01:15:16,790
Lead the men to the far side of the island.

741
01:15:17,170 --> 01:15:18,160
Gobber, go with the men.

742
01:15:18,220 --> 01:15:21,210
I think I'll stay, just in case you're thinking of doing something crazy.

743
01:15:21,270 --> 01:15:24,490
I can buy them a few minutes if I give that thing something to hunt for.

744
01:15:24,890 --> 01:15:27,310
Then I can double that time.

745
01:15:28,390 --> 01:15:31,970
- Here!  - Oh, no. Here!

746
01:15:43,630 --> 01:15:46,650
- Fight me!  - No, me!

747
01:15:53,680 --> 01:15:55,620
Ruff, Tuff, watch your backs!

748
01:15:56,370 --> 01:15:57,400
Move, Fishlegs!

749
01:15:58,540 --> 01:16:02,380
Look at us! We're on dragons! We're on dragons! All of us!

750
01:16:06,810 --> 01:16:11,200
Every bit the bull-headed stubborn Viking you ever were.

751
01:16:12,970 --> 01:16:14,600
- Fishlegs, break it down!  - Okay.

752
01:16:15,010 --> 01:16:18,720
Heavily armored skull and tail made for bashing and crushing. Steer clear of both.

753
01:16:18,810 --> 01:16:22,190
Small eyes, large nostrils. Relies on hearing and smell.

754
01:16:22,210 --> 01:16:26,270
Okay, Lout, Legs, hang in its blind spot. Make some noise. Keep it confused.

755
01:16:26,300 --> 01:16:29,300
Ruff, Tuff, find out if it has a shot limit. Make it mad.

756
01:16:29,850 --> 01:16:31,790
- That's my specialty!  - Since when?

757
01:16:31,850 --> 01:16:33,670
Everyone knows I'm more irritating, see.

758
01:16:34,800 --> 01:16:37,560
Just do what I told you. I'll be back as soon as I can.

759
01:16:38,370 --> 01:16:39,980
Don't worry! We got it covered!

760
01:16:40,020 --> 01:16:41,230
Yeah!

761
01:16:49,040 --> 01:16:50,340
- Fool!  - Butto!

762
01:16:50,370 --> 01:16:51,700
Bye, ya Grendel!

763
01:16:57,950 --> 01:17:00,330
Um, this thing doesn't have a blind spot!

764
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:04,100
There!

765
01:17:13,020 --> 01:17:14,160
Go help the others!

766
01:17:15,650 --> 01:17:16,700
Okay, hold on. Hold on.

767
01:17:21,070 --> 01:17:23,710
- It's working!  - Yeah, it's working!

768
01:17:33,630 --> 01:17:37,350
I've lost power on the Gronckle! Snotlout, do something!

769
01:17:39,770 --> 01:17:40,680
I'm okay!

770
01:17:41,530 --> 01:17:42,980
Less okay.

771
01:17:45,990 --> 01:17:49,550
I can't miss! What's wrong, buddy? You got something in your eye?

772
01:17:53,470 --> 01:17:55,430
Yeah, you're the Viking!

773
01:18:01,390 --> 01:18:02,300
Woah!

774
01:18:33,150 --> 01:18:34,410
Dad?

775
01:18:53,560 --> 01:18:54,680
You got it, buddy!

776
01:18:56,740 --> 01:18:57,540
Hiccup!

777
01:19:00,360 --> 01:19:01,050
I'm sorry...

778
01:19:02,390 --> 01:19:03,580
for... for everything.

779
01:19:04,330 --> 01:19:05,520
Yeah... me too.

780
01:19:05,560 --> 01:19:07,140
You don't have to go up there.

781
01:19:08,140 --> 01:19:11,260
We're Vikings. It's an occupational hazard...

782
01:19:12,450 --> 01:19:15,010
I'm proud to call you my son.

783
01:19:17,010 --> 01:19:18,380
Thanks, Dad.

784
01:19:24,200 --> 01:19:25,140
He's up!

785
01:19:28,870 --> 01:19:30,280
Get Snotlout outta there!

786
01:19:30,390 --> 01:19:31,600
- I'm on it!  - I'm on it first!

787
01:19:31,700 --> 01:19:33,820
Hey, let me drive!

788
01:19:34,830 --> 01:19:36,850
- Don't push me!  - I'll push your teeth out!

789
01:19:40,540 --> 01:19:42,240
You know, I can't believe that worked.

790
01:19:50,370 --> 01:19:52,940
- Night Fury!  - Get down!

791
01:20:03,820 --> 01:20:04,820
Did you get her?

792
01:20:14,750 --> 01:20:15,330
Go!

793
01:20:15,700 --> 01:20:20,120
This thing has wings. Okay, let's see if it can use them!

794
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:37,950
You think that did it?

795
01:20:43,520 --> 01:20:44,860
Well, he can fly.

796
01:21:06,040 --> 01:21:10,200
Okay, Toothless, time to disappear! Come on, bud!

797
01:21:16,570 --> 01:21:17,940
Here it comes!

798
01:22:09,980 --> 01:22:11,120
Watch out!

799
01:22:13,290 --> 01:22:15,960
Okay, time's up. Let's see if this works.

800
01:22:18,940 --> 01:22:20,950
Come on! Is that the best you can do?

801
01:22:38,780 --> 01:22:41,440
Stay with me, buddy. We're good. Just a little bit longer.

802
01:22:46,080 --> 01:22:49,570
Hold, Toothless. Now!

803
01:23:13,370 --> 01:23:15,960
No... No!

804
01:23:32,240 --> 01:23:35,980
Hiccup! Hiccup!

805
01:23:37,770 --> 01:23:38,860
Son!

806
01:23:41,630 --> 01:23:42,590
Hiccup!

807
01:24:04,120 --> 01:24:05,360
Oh son!

808
01:24:07,270 --> 01:24:08,610
I did this.

809
01:24:39,150 --> 01:24:42,940
I'm s... I'm so sorry.

810
01:24:48,780 --> 01:24:49,800
Hiccup!

811
01:24:56,570 --> 01:24:59,940
He's alive! You brought him back alive!

812
01:25:16,850 --> 01:25:19,890
Thank you... for saving my son.

813
01:25:20,700 --> 01:25:23,960
Well, you know, most of him.

814
01:25:41,920 --> 01:25:43,420
Hey, Toothless.

815
01:25:44,630 --> 01:25:46,470
Happy to see you too, buddy.

816
01:25:47,170 --> 01:25:51,700
Aawww, what... uh... I'm... in my house

817
01:25:53,480 --> 01:25:54,820
You're in my house.

818
01:25:55,730 --> 01:25:57,290
Does my dad know you're here?

819
01:25:57,460 --> 01:25:59,400
Uh, what, oh, okay... okay.

820
01:26:00,530 --> 01:26:04,160
Toothless, no. Toothless! Aw, come on.

821
01:26:42,540 --> 01:26:44,840
Okay. Thanks, bud.

822
01:26:55,920 --> 01:26:57,760
Toothless, stay here.

823
01:26:58,170 --> 01:27:01,260
C'mon guys. Get ready! Hold on tight. Here we go!

824
01:27:03,860 --> 01:27:05,060
What?

825
01:27:13,940 --> 01:27:16,020
I knew it. I'm dead.

826
01:27:16,920 --> 01:27:19,020
No, but you give it your best shot.

827
01:27:19,110 --> 01:27:21,010
So, what do you think?

828
01:27:21,040 --> 01:27:22,670
Hey look, it's Hiccup!

829
01:27:24,440 --> 01:27:25,110
Hiccup!

830
01:27:27,330 --> 01:27:31,350
It turns out, all we needed was a little more of... this.

831
01:27:31,700 --> 01:27:33,600
You just gestured to all of me?

832
01:27:34,560 --> 01:27:38,000
Well, most of you. That bit's my handiwork.

833
01:27:38,110 --> 01:27:41,510
With a little Hiccup flare thrown in. You think that'll do?

834
01:27:41,950 --> 01:27:43,880
I might make a few tweaks.

835
01:27:45,290 --> 01:27:47,580
That's... for scaring me.

836
01:27:47,680 --> 01:27:50,080
What... what, is it always going to be this way? Because...

837
01:27:53,180 --> 01:27:54,560
I could get used to it.

838
01:27:57,830 --> 01:27:59,420
Welcome home.

839
01:27:59,660 --> 01:28:01,870
- Night Fury!  - Get down!

840
01:28:13,360 --> 01:28:14,680
You ready?

841
01:28:17,170 --> 01:28:18,970
This is Berk...

842
01:28:19,770 --> 01:28:23,690
It snows nine months of the year and hails the other three.

843
01:28:25,340 --> 01:28:28,200
Any food that grows here is tough and tasteless.

844
01:28:30,590 --> 01:28:33,490
The people that grow here are even more so.

845
01:28:37,280 --> 01:28:39,980
The only upsides are the pets.

846
01:28:42,750 --> 01:28:45,970
While other places have ponies or parrots...

847
01:28:47,900 --> 01:28:49,090
We have...

848
01:28:50,350 --> 01:28:52,000
Dragons.

